    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Indemnification, you say?  It's a fancy word for a promise, a sort of legal shield, and it's all about who takes the blame when things go sideways.  Basically, it means you agree to cover the other party's losses if something goes wrong because of *your* work. Think of it like this: if your freelance project causes a legal headache for the client, you're agreeing to step in and pay for the mess. It’s a very important clause, so don't just skim it!",
      "source": "target",
